  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf \u0dbb\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2-\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3 \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Iranavila sea becomes rough-many houses lost to the sea",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Fishermen say that the Iranavila beach screen is being severely eroded with the bad weather conditions.",
        "Fishermen say that almost one kilometer of the sea screen of Iranavila has been destroyed due to sea erosion.",
        "With the sea erosion, many houses located near the beach screen have been affected by the sea erosion and many coconut trees are also being swept into the sea, people say.",
        "It is said that with the erosion of the sea, the sea road from Halavata to Vaikkala, which is located on the coastal screen, is also in serious danger.",
        "In view of all this, they say that it is difficult for them to put a fishing vessel on the shore to go to and from the fishing boats."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Iranavila sea",
          "label": "PERSON"
        }
      ],
